nincluding longitudinal modes and illustrate these arguments with numerical\nsimulations in higher dimensions. We find that the bandwidth of the radio\nsignal is dominated by Doppler broadening from the relative motion of the\nneutron star with respect to the observer. Therefore, we conclude that the\nradio signal from the resonant decay is weaker than previously thought, which\nmeans one relies on local density peaks to probe weaker axion-photon couplings.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 25 Oct 2019 19:28:43 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 6 Nov 2019 15:06:34 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 17 Jun 2020 21:43:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-07-15"}
